      • getSpatialContext

        public org.locationtech.spatial4j.context.SpatialContext getSpatialContext()
        Get the underlying SpatialContext. This should not be needed by most clients but if you need to interact with the underlying libraries this is your access to it. For example, create a shape manually: 
        
   ShapeFactory sf = gu.getSpatialContext().getShapeFactory();
   LineStringBuilder builder = sf.lineString();
   builder.pointXY(someX, someY);
   builder.pointXY(anotherX, anotherY);
   Shape lineBetweenPoints = builder.build();
        Returns:
        SpatialContext the underlying spatial context

      • getCentroid

        public org.locationtech.spatial4j.shape.Point getCentroid(org.locationtech.spatial4j.shape.Shape geometry)
        Return a Point representing the centroid of the given Shape. If the Shape is a Point, the returned Point will be identical to the Point passed in. If the Shape passed in is a Line, the Point returned will be the midpoint of the Line, and will be on the line. If the Shape passed in is a Polygon the Point returned will be the centroid of the Polygon, but may not be contained inside the polygon in the case of a Polygon with a 'donut hole' in the middle, or a 'U' shaped Polygon, etc.
        Parameters:
        geometry - The Shape to calculate the centroid of.
        Returns:
        a Point representing the centroid of this Shape.

      • calculateArea

        public double calculateArea(org.locationtech.spatial4j.shape.Shape geometry)
        Calculate the area of the give Shape in square meters. By definition if the Shape passed in is a Point or Line this method will return 0.0. Only Polygons have Area. This calculation assumes a spherical earth, in fact the earth is ellipsoidal, which will cause this estimate to be accurate to approximately .3%. More information here
        Parameters:
        geometry - Shape to calculate area of
        Returns:
        The Area of the Shape in square meters

      • getIntersection

        public org.locationtech.spatial4j.shape.Shape getIntersection(org.locationtech.spatial4j.shape.Shape s1,
                                                              org.locationtech.spatial4j.shape.Shape s2)
        Return a Shape representing the area of intersection between the two provided Shapes. By definition the intersection of a Point within a Polygon is the Point, or a Line within a Polygon is the portion of the Line that is contained within the Polygon.
        Parameters:
        s1 - Shape 1
        s2 - Shape 2
        Returns:
        The Shape of overlap between the two provided Shapes, or an empty Shape if there is no overlap (does not return null in that case)

      • getIntersectionArea

        public double getIntersectionArea(org.locationtech.spatial4j.shape.Shape s1,
                                  org.locationtech.spatial4j.shape.Shape s2)
        Get the area of the intersection of the two provided Shapes in square Meters. By definition the intersection of a Point with anything or a Line with anything will return 0.0, as Lines and Points have no area.
        Parameters:
        s1 - Shape 1
        s2 - Shape 2
        Returns:
        The area of overlap between the two shapes in square meters

      • relocate

        public org.locationtech.spatial4j.shape.Shape relocate(org.locationtech.spatial4j.shape.Shape src,
                                                       org.locationtech.spatial4j.shape.Shape dest)
        Move the Shape src to the location of Shape dest. More specifically, move the centroid of src to the locaiton of the centroid of dest. Although the primary use case of this is to compare Shapes similarity regardless of relative location note that there is no guarantee that the relocated shape will have more overlap than pre-relocation.
        Parameters:
        src - The shape to relocate
        dest - The shape that provides the location to move src to.
        Returns:
        a new Shape that is identical to src, but relocated so that its centroid is now located at the centroid of dest

      • getHausdorffSimilarity

        public double getHausdorffSimilarity(org.locationtech.spatial4j.shape.Shape s1,
                                     org.locationtech.spatial4j.shape.Shape s2)
        Measures the degree of similarity between two Geometrys using the Hausdorff distance metric. The measure is normalized to lie in the range [0, 1]. Higher measures indicate a greater degree of similarity.

        The measure is computed by computing the Hausdorff distance between the input geometries, and then normalizing this by dividing it by the diagonal distance across the envelope of the combined geometries.

        Parameters:
        s1 - Shape 1
        s2 - Shape 2
        Returns:
        Hausdorff Similarity normalized to [0, 1]
